8. Risk Philosophy
The central purpose of the Feasibility Study is the early and systematic retirement of risk. This includes technical risk, layout and constructability risk, throughput uncertainty, and cost exposure. By resolving these matters prior to FEED, the project materially reduces downstream rework, programme delay, and capital escalation.
